('LOC_DB_SCIENCE_PER_POP_DISABLED_NAME', 'Disabled', 'en_US'),

('LOC_DB_SCIENCE_PER_POP_DESC', 'The amount of science each population in your cities inherently generates (i.e. generated without help from districts, buildings, worked tiles, governors, policies etc.). Without this mod, it would be 0.50 (or 0.70 if playing without Rise & Fall or Gathering Storm). I believe it should be 0.30 or lower so that players have to earn science, not just automatically get it from growing cities. This also slows down tech tree progress so that you aren''t developing nukes in the 1800s. A slowing effect is definitely needed when playing with the "Learn From Other Civs" option.{LOC_DB_GOLD_MOD_NOTE}', 'en_US'),
('LOC_DB_SCIENCE_PER_POP_LABEL', 'Science Per Population', 'en_US'),
('LOC_DB_SCIENCE_PER_POP_NAME', 'Science Per Population', 'en_US'),

('LOC_DB_SIEGE_UNITS_NO_EXTRA_MOVEMENT_DESC', '[ICON_Bullet]Siege units don''t get movement bonuses from things like Great Generals or Logistics, because when they do, they can move & shoot. (They''re supposed to have the Expert Crew promotion to be able to do that.)[NEWLINE][ICON_Bullet]The Expert Crew promotion provides +1 movement in addition to the moving and shooting ability{LOC_DB_GOLD_MOD_NOTE}', 'en_US'),
('LOC_DB_SIEGE_UNITS_NO_EXTRA_MOVEMENT_NAME', 'Siege Units: No Extra Movement', 'en_US'),

('LOC_DB_SOLI_DEO_GLORIA_DESC', 'Makes religion competitive, fun, and historical. Normally, religion is largely ignore-able. Holy Sites are a waste of a valuable district slot that could be a Campus or Harbor. The point of this mod is to make religion fun and make players pause before passing over a Holy Site. I don''t want religious strategies to super-dominate... just want them to have a place at the table.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Details:[NEWLINE][ICON_Bullet]There is no limit to the number of religions; every civilization (except Kongo) can found its own religion.[NEWLINE][ICON_Bullet]There is no limit to the number of beliefs you can have in your religion, and the beliefs are not grouped into "classes". This makes religion interesting to all victory types. Even if don''t want to spam Missionaries, you might want to found a religion to get bonuses for combat strength, housing, amenities, science, culture, etc.[NEWLINE][ICON_Bullet]The religious beliefs were all replaced. The new beliefs are such that they improve every city that follows the religion (never just giving a benefit to the founder only). This introduces a strategic element to spreading your religion, because as you do that you also spread its benefits. If your opponent has been neglecting religion altogether while your religion banks a ton of gold each turn with beliefs like "Acres of Diamond" and "Treasures In Heaven", converting his cities will make him rich at no effort on his part.[NEWLINE][ICON_Bullet]Great Prophets are just like the other Great People. Instead of getting only one to found your religion, with SDG, you can earn subsequent Great Prophets who each add a belief to your religion. (Hence, Great Prophet points have a function beyond founding your religion.)[NEWLINE][ICON_Bullet]Great Prophets act like religious Great Generals... they give your nearby religious units +1 movement and +5 combat strength.[NEWLINE][ICON_Bullet]Warrior Monks no longer require a belief. They can be built from Temples by anyone.[NEWLINE][ICON_Bullet]Lots of color was added to religion. Boring and generic terms were turned into more flavorful ones. There are references to polygamy, cargo cults, and "turtles all the way down". Read the civilopedia entries on the religious beliefs. I spent a lot of time on them.{LOC_DB_GOLD_MOD_NOTE}{LOC_DB_XP1_NOTE}', 'en_US'),
('LOC_DB_SOLI_DEO_GLORIA_NAME', 'Soli Deo Gloria', 'en_US'),

('LOC_DB_THEATER_SQUARE_BETTER_ADJACENCIES_DESC', 'Theater Squares get +1 culture for each adjacent district (instead of +1 culture for every two), +1 culture when placed on a tile with Charming Appeal, and +2 culture when placed on a tile with Breathtaking Appeal. They still have their adjacencies for wonders (+2), Entertainment Districts (+2), and Water Parks (+2). Makes Theater Squares more desirable.{LOC_DB_GOLD_MOD_NOTE}', 'en_US'),
('LOC_DB_THEATER_SQUARE_BETTER_ADJACENCIES_NAME', 'Theater Squares: Better Adjacencies', 'en_US'),

('LOC_DESC_DB_TEAM_ADJUSTMENTS', 'Gameplay adjustments for team games:[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Players can form diplomatic alliances from turn 1[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]City States don''t enforce their borders (anyone can walk on their tiles). This avoids the complication where my teammate is suzerain and yet I can''t go on the city-state''s tiles without declaring war on the CS.[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Learn From Other Civs: Removes the bonus % from alliances, friendship, open borders, joint wars, and defense pacts (because in team games you get a boost from your teammates when they discover a tech/civic){LOC_DB_GOLD_MOD_NOTE}', 'en_US'),
('LOC_NAME_DB_TEAM_ADJUSTMENTS', 'Team Adjustments', 'en_US'),

('LOC_DB_TREES_HIDE_UNITS_DESC', 'Ever wonder why an archer from two tiles away can shoot your scout while he''s hiding in a forest? With this option, any unit on a woods or rainforest tile automatically is hidden (like a privateer)... meaning they are only visible to enemy units in adjacent tiles or units that have an ability to see hidden units (like a scout).{LOC_DB_GOLD_MOD_NOTE}', 'en_US'),
('LOC_DB_TREES_HIDE_UNITS_NAME', 'Trees Hide Units', 'en_US'),

('LOC_DB_TURNS_FOR_PEACE_05_DESC', 'Peace treaties, friendships, and alliances are 17% as long as normal (5 turns on Standard game speed){LOC_DB_GOLD_MOD_NOTE}', 'en_US'),
('LOC_DB_TURNS_FOR_PEACE_05_NAME', '17% (5 turns on Standard speed)', 'en_US'),
('LOC_DB_TURNS_FOR_PEACE_10_DESC', 'Peace treaties, friendships, and alliances are 33% as long as normal (10 turns on Standard game speed){LOC_DB_GOLD_MOD_NOTE}', 'en_US'),
('LOC_DB_TURNS_FOR_PEACE_10_NAME', '33% (10 turns on Standard speed)', 'en_US'),
('LOC_DB_TURNS_FOR_PEACE_15_DESC', 'Peace treaties, friendships, and alliances are 50% as long as normal (15 turns on Standard game speed){LOC_DB_GOLD_MOD_NOTE}', 'en_US'),
